    {
        "content": "<p>Great! Though it looks like if you switch to <code>central_longitude=0</code> with that code you posted above, the white line does reappear. I think this is a side effect of using <code>.contourf</code>, which is why the white space doesn't show up with the built in <code>.plot</code> which uses pcolormesh (I think). </p>\n<p>And I see what you mean about the axis/colorbar formatting. xarray's <a href=\"https://docs.xarray.dev/en/stable/user-guide/plotting.html\">built-in plotting</a> is great , but I usually switch over to cartopy/matplotlib if I want to make things more customized, especially with map projections. But this could be a great area for future contributions to xarray!</p>",
